1
00:00:10,533 --> 00:00:12,267
<i>I'm going to assign you a case,</i>

2
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:14,500
<i>it's Lieutenant Robles' sniper.</i>

3
00:00:14,633 --> 00:00:17,100
<i>Bautista, I want you
to take the lead.</i>

4
00:00:17,233 --> 00:00:20,200
<i>So we can see if you learned
anything from Garcia.</i>

5
00:00:20,333 --> 00:00:21,600
<i>You asked us so many questions,</i>

6
00:00:21,733 --> 00:00:23,500
<i> you even asked our ID,</i>

7
00:00:23,633 --> 00:00:26,033
<i>and the people we want to talk
with are not here either.</i>

8
00:00:26,167 --> 00:00:29,200
<i>There were two police officers
here earlier, asking about you.</i>

9
00:00:29,333 --> 00:00:31,000
<i>I'll be careful,
no one will know the truth.</i>

10
00:00:31,133 --> 00:00:32,800
<i>Are you going to wait for Jared
to come out,</i>

11
00:00:32,933 --> 00:00:34,700
<i> then just go after him?</i>

12
00:00:34,867 --> 00:00:35,900
<i> My point is,</i>

13
00:00:36,033 --> 00:00:39,100
<i>you shouldn't mix jealousy
and work.</i>

14
00:00:39,233 --> 00:00:40,667
<i>That's not true,
we're not yet a couple.</i>

15
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:42,300
<i>- What? What about Sir Eric?
- What about Sir Eric?</i>

16
00:00:42,433 --> 00:00:45,867
<i>- Selena...
- No, oh, we were just talking.</i>

17
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:47,900
<i>How about you and Sir Tonyo,
Ma'am Bobby,</i>

18
00:00:48,033 --> 00:00:49,167
<i> are you talking again?</i>

19
00:00:49,300 --> 00:00:50,533
<i> Bobby, who is Tonyo?</i>

20
00:00:50,667 --> 00:00:51,700
<i> Is he your boyfriend?</i>

21
00:00:51,833 --> 00:00:52,933
<i>- Yes!
- Yes!</i>

22
00:00:53,067 --> 00:00:55,067
<i>Boss, do you know
where the Mayor is going?</i>

23
00:00:55,200 --> 00:00:57,633
<i>To the Binibining
Calabari event, Sir.</i>

24
00:00:57,767 --> 00:01:00,800
<i>Stop! Ladies,
if you walk like this,</i>

25
00:01:00,933 --> 00:01:02,633
<i>you're definitely going to lose.</i>

26
00:01:02,767 --> 00:01:04,800
<i> Let me show you how it's done.</i>

27
00:01:04,933 --> 00:01:07,667
<i>What's with you? I told you to
move to the left!</i>

28
00:01:09,767 --> 00:01:10,967
<i> Auntie!</i>

29
00:01:16,367 --> 00:01:18,467
- Mom! Mom! Mom!
- No!

30
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:19,533
Auntie, are you okay?

31
00:01:19,667 --> 00:01:21,233
- No, hija.
- What happened?

32
00:01:21,367 --> 00:01:23,533
- That bastard, she pushed me!
- Okay, wait, wait.

33
00:01:23,667 --> 00:01:24,933
- Let's, let's go inside...
- I didn't do...

34
00:01:25,067 --> 00:01:26,333
Let's go inside, might get sick.

35
00:01:26,467 --> 00:01:27,600
Oh my!

36
00:01:27,733 --> 00:01:29,167
- I'm not done with you yet!
- Ma'am, I really didn't...

37
00:01:29,300 --> 00:01:30,700
- Let's go inside, come on.
- What now?

38
00:01:30,833 --> 00:01:32,233
Oh, my goodness!

39
00:01:34,867 --> 00:01:38,200
All right, ladies, so that's the
end of our orientation today.

40
00:01:38,333 --> 00:01:39,900
Oh, you've all done wonderfully

41
00:01:40,033 --> 00:01:41,500
I'll see you tomorrow.

42
00:01:41,667 --> 00:01:43,400
So good luck to you
and be careful.

43
00:01:43,533 --> 00:01:44,867
Okay, good job, ladies.

44
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:46,667
- Are you okay?
- Thank you!

45
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:50,667
Oh my Bobby, you pushed Tita.

46
00:01:50,800 --> 00:01:54,367
No, I just dodged,
I didn't push her.

47
00:01:54,500 --> 00:01:57,633
I'm sure that's what she thinks
too, so good luck!

48
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:03,967
Ma'am, Maestra is really
picking on you, isn't she?

49
00:02:04,100 --> 00:02:06,400
And so is Charlie.

50
00:02:06,533 --> 00:02:07,567
Let her be.

51
00:02:07,700 --> 00:02:08,667
I'm not paying attention
to her anymore.

52
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:10,867
But Maestra went
swimming, right?

53
00:02:12,733 --> 00:02:14,767
I thought she was going to walk
in the catwalk, but she jumped.

54
00:02:14,933 --> 00:02:17,333
Did you see her fall earlier?

55
00:02:17,467 --> 00:02:19,567
I thought she'll do
butterfly strokes.

56
00:02:19,700 --> 00:02:21,200
That's enough,
If she returns,

57
00:02:21,333 --> 00:02:22,600
for sure she'll pick
on me again.

58
00:02:22,733 --> 00:02:24,567
Her head must have
cooled down, right?

59
00:02:24,700 --> 00:02:25,733
That's cold.

60
00:02:25,867 --> 00:02:27,633
She said, "To the left".

61
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:00,700
Doc, thank you for coming.

62
00:03:00,833 --> 00:03:01,967
You even made an effort.

63
00:03:02,100 --> 00:03:03,767
It's okay.

64
00:03:03,900 --> 00:03:05,033
I do whatever I can to help.

65
00:03:05,167 --> 00:03:08,000
And besides, I also want this
case to be over.

66
00:03:09,067 --> 00:03:10,433
Look at this.

67
00:03:13,667 --> 00:03:16,533
What's this, Doc?
Oh, this is a ballistic report.

68
00:03:16,667 --> 00:03:18,100
Yes, that's right.

69
00:03:19,433 --> 00:03:21,833
Based on the ballistic report
and trajectory

70
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:23,833
of the shooting of Regan,

71
00:03:23,967 --> 00:03:26,867
the bullet came
from somewhere high.

72
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:30,833
That means that one of
the rooftops around Station 12,

73
00:03:30,967 --> 00:03:32,500
the shooter was positioned.

74
00:03:32,633 --> 00:03:35,567
Thank you, Doc,
this is a big help to us.

75
00:03:35,700 --> 00:03:37,133
Anytime.

76
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:41,500
Mom...

77
00:03:42,433 --> 00:03:45,567
Mom, I know you're the one who
started the trouble earlier.

78
00:03:45,700 --> 00:03:47,700
What? What do you mean
it was me?

79
00:03:47,833 --> 00:03:50,233
You don't really believe me
anymore, do you?

80
00:03:50,367 --> 00:03:52,633
I'm getting irritated
with that Bobby.

81
00:03:52,767 --> 00:03:55,067
Why is she there
where I am too?

82
00:03:55,233 --> 00:03:58,433
She really wants to piss me off,
doesn't she?

83
00:03:58,567 --> 00:04:01,667
Mom, this has to stop.

84
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:04,567
What? What do you mean?

85
00:04:04,700 --> 00:04:09,300
Mom, I know you're pissed off
at Bobby,

86
00:04:09,433 --> 00:04:11,700
and I think it would be better
for you to know...

87
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:17,400
that Bobby and Charlie,

88
00:04:17,533 --> 00:04:20,933
they're not here because of you.

89
00:04:21,067 --> 00:04:24,600
They're not here
for the pageant also.

90
00:04:24,733 --> 00:04:26,600
They're here...

91
00:04:29,633 --> 00:04:30,900
because they're investigating

92
00:04:31,033 --> 00:04:33,500
the murder case
Cecilia mentioned.

93
00:04:35,267 --> 00:04:39,400
If I were you,
stay clear of Bobby.

94
00:04:39,533 --> 00:04:41,200
You might get caught up
in the investigation

95
00:04:41,333 --> 00:04:42,867
they're doing.

96
00:04:48,300 --> 00:04:50,200
And yes, Mom,

97
00:04:50,333 --> 00:04:52,467
I don't believe in you.

98
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:58,867
You started it.

99
00:05:02,133 --> 00:05:03,467
- Oh, come on.
- Hey, Vince!

100
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:05,100
Dude, someone's looking for you.

101
00:05:05,233 --> 00:05:06,400
Who is it?

102
00:05:08,867 --> 00:05:10,233
Faye...

103
00:05:10,367 --> 00:05:11,700
What are you doing here?

104
00:05:11,833 --> 00:05:14,233
Let's talk.

105
00:05:14,367 --> 00:05:16,300
Because, Vince,
I don't understand anymore.

106
00:05:16,433 --> 00:05:18,533
What's happening between us
doesn't make sense anymore.

107
00:05:21,467 --> 00:05:23,533
Vince, just admit it to me.

108
00:05:23,667 --> 00:05:26,500
Vince, what's going on between
the two of us?

109
00:05:26,633 --> 00:05:31,067
I don't understand why we're all
like this all of a sudden.

110
00:05:31,200 --> 00:05:33,700
You're not answering my texts,
my calls.

111
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:35,400
You're avoiding me.

112
00:05:35,567 --> 00:05:37,667
What is it?

113
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:38,967
Vince!

114
00:05:39,100 --> 00:05:40,100
I've been thinking about all
sorts of things

115
00:05:40,233 --> 00:05:43,067
just to make sense of all this!

116
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:44,400
What?

117
00:05:44,533 --> 00:05:45,667
Is it because of
what happened to you

118
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:48,100
the night you got beaten up,
Vince?

119
00:05:48,233 --> 00:05:50,533
Because, Vince, since then,
you've changed.

120
00:05:50,667 --> 00:05:52,633
Talk to me!

121
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:58,100
Does Glen have anything
to do with this?

122
00:05:58,233 --> 00:05:59,600
Nothing!

123
00:05:59,733 --> 00:06:00,933
Why are you even
thinking about that?

124
00:06:01,067 --> 00:06:02,533
Oh, what's wrong?

125
00:06:02,667 --> 00:06:05,267
Don't you want me anymore? What?

126
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:05,867
Faye...

127
00:06:07,233 --> 00:06:09,767
I'm too handsome
not to want you.

128
00:06:11,700 --> 00:06:12,767
Faye, the truth is...

129
00:06:14,967 --> 00:06:16,433
I miss you so much.

130
00:06:16,567 --> 00:06:18,300
Oh, what's wrong?

131
00:06:18,433 --> 00:06:20,400
Can we go back to the way
things were?

132
00:06:23,067 --> 00:06:24,600
Faye...

133
00:06:30,300 --> 00:06:30,900
just...

134
00:06:32,133 --> 00:06:35,167
remember this.

135
00:06:35,300 --> 00:06:36,733
Everything I do,

136
00:06:36,867 --> 00:06:40,000
everything I will do,

137
00:06:40,133 --> 00:06:42,433
is for us.

138
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:44,600
Maybe...

139
00:06:44,733 --> 00:06:46,133
the best thing
we can do for now...

140
00:06:47,867 --> 00:06:49,533
is not to see each other again.

141
00:06:51,700 --> 00:06:53,800
What?

142
00:06:53,933 --> 00:06:56,033
Can you trust me?

143
00:07:01,300 --> 00:07:02,800
Faye, just...

144
00:07:03,633 --> 00:07:05,133
trust me.

145
00:07:06,900 --> 00:07:09,000
You're the only woman
in my heart.

146
00:07:16,233 --> 00:07:19,667
No one knows about this
prostitution we're doing.

147
00:07:21,133 --> 00:07:22,500
But remember this.

148
00:07:24,167 --> 00:07:28,467
Just make sure you don't get
caught for killing Donabel.

149
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:35,767
If you get caught, I'm sorry.

150
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:15,533
Where is he?

151
00:08:18,967 --> 00:08:20,667
Is it me you're looking for?

152
00:08:38,567 --> 00:08:39,667
What?

153
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:41,467
Are you looking for me?

154
00:08:44,433 --> 00:08:46,600
Why would I look for you?

155
00:08:46,733 --> 00:08:48,400
I don't know you.

156
00:08:50,867 --> 00:08:53,967
Is there anything funny?

157
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:56,633
You're a fool too, aren't you?

158
00:08:56,800 --> 00:08:58,500
What did you say?

159
00:08:58,633 --> 00:09:01,600
I know you meant to bump
into me yesterday, Dude.

160
00:09:01,733 --> 00:09:03,233
I'm not numb.

161
00:09:05,133 --> 00:09:06,100
So?

162
00:09:06,233 --> 00:09:07,733
I have to go ahead.

163
00:09:07,867 --> 00:09:11,533
The contestants are going to
have swimsuit fittings.

164
00:09:11,667 --> 00:09:13,800
Maybe you want
to watch Bobby too?

165
00:09:13,933 --> 00:09:15,333
Do you want to?

166
00:09:15,467 --> 00:09:17,133
Oh...

167
00:09:17,267 --> 00:09:19,700
Oh, sorry.

168
00:09:19,833 --> 00:09:23,100
Only staff and sponsors
are allowed.

169
00:09:23,233 --> 00:09:24,667
Too bad.

170
00:09:24,800 --> 00:09:26,233
Next time.

171
00:09:28,933 --> 00:09:30,400
Jared!

172
00:09:37,333 --> 00:09:38,633
- I want something different.
- Like this.

173
00:09:38,767 --> 00:09:41,000
Round, oh.
Oh, really round, see.

174
00:09:41,133 --> 00:09:42,467
That's the kind who scrambles
over me before.

175
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:45,267
What, did you bring
Miss Faye home?

176
00:09:45,400 --> 00:09:47,233
Yes, I took her home already.

177
00:09:47,367 --> 00:09:48,767
You're something else, Bro.

178
00:09:48,900 --> 00:09:50,400
You've got some nerve.

179
00:09:50,533 --> 00:09:52,700
Imagine, the woman goes to you.

180
00:09:52,833 --> 00:09:54,633
- He's handsome, right?
- Really handsome!

181
00:09:54,767 --> 00:09:56,033
Get serious.

182
00:09:56,167 --> 00:09:57,967
What we've been
through is serious.

183
00:09:58,100 --> 00:09:59,233
What's your plan?

184
00:09:59,367 --> 00:10:02,067
I will find out if it was really
mayor who had me beaten up.

185
00:10:02,233 --> 00:10:04,833
Oh my, that's dangerous, Bro.

186
00:10:04,967 --> 00:10:06,833
That's difficult!

187
00:10:06,967 --> 00:10:08,467
But don't worry,

188
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:10,533
we'll be with you until the end.

189
00:10:14,533 --> 00:10:15,967
What, Tonyo?

190
00:10:16,100 --> 00:10:17,733
Are you going
to say anything else?

191
00:10:20,400 --> 00:10:23,567
I know you're hiding something,
Jared.

192
00:10:23,700 --> 00:10:25,733
What do you mean?

193
00:10:25,867 --> 00:10:27,300
Care to elaborate?

194
00:10:30,533 --> 00:10:35,700
I know you're not
the CEO of Add2Cart.

195
00:10:35,867 --> 00:10:41,067
That's a very serious
accusation, Lieutenant Conde.

196
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:45,200
You know, Addison
called me earlier.

197
00:10:45,333 --> 00:10:47,000
Addison Lee-Cartega,

198
00:10:47,133 --> 00:10:49,800
CFO of Add2Cart.

199
00:10:49,933 --> 00:10:51,867
She said you guys
were asking about me.

200
00:10:54,067 --> 00:10:55,833
Check with the office.

201
00:10:55,967 --> 00:10:57,433
Addison Lee-Cartega.

202
00:10:57,567 --> 00:10:59,867
That's our CFO.

203
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:02,167
Then, why would she call me?

204
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:05,567
You know, Tonyo,

205
00:11:05,700 --> 00:11:08,100
just because the receptionist
doesn't know me...

206
00:11:08,267 --> 00:11:10,200
doesn't mean I'm not the CEO.

207
00:11:12,367 --> 00:11:14,667
Now, if you want
to clarify something,

208
00:11:14,800 --> 00:11:17,233
say it because I have to go.

209
00:11:17,367 --> 00:11:20,067
No matter what you say,

210
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:23,833
I am not wrong with my hunches.

211
00:11:23,967 --> 00:11:26,433
You're hiding something.

212
00:11:26,567 --> 00:11:29,300
So my advice to you

213
00:11:29,433 --> 00:11:31,300
is to stay away from Bobby.

214
00:11:45,433 --> 00:11:46,967
What do you think, Torres?

215
00:11:47,100 --> 00:11:49,867
Maybe, the sniper might actually
be stationed here.

216
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:51,833
Well, from the direction
Doc pointed out,

217
00:11:51,967 --> 00:11:55,200
this is the best vantage point.

218
00:11:55,333 --> 00:11:57,000
Speaking of Doc...

219
00:11:57,133 --> 00:11:59,067
Doc is really lucky, isn't she?

220
00:11:59,200 --> 00:12:01,433
Think about it, Bautista,
your boyfriend is the Mayor.

221
00:12:01,567 --> 00:12:02,600
Who knows, in the long run

222
00:12:02,733 --> 00:12:04,333
she'll even become
the first lady of Calabari.

223
00:12:04,467 --> 00:12:06,133
Are you going to let her go?

224
00:12:06,267 --> 00:12:07,667
You really think like that,
don't you?

225
00:12:07,800 --> 00:12:09,167
What did I say wrong?

226
00:12:09,300 --> 00:12:11,633
Doc is the only one who's really
lucky between the two of them?

227
00:12:11,767 --> 00:12:14,067
Isn't Mayor also lucky with Doc?

228
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:17,000
I'm not saying Mayor
isn't lucky with Doc.

229
00:12:17,167 --> 00:12:18,800
It's the same thing.

230
00:12:18,933 --> 00:12:21,300
Think about it,
Doc is very intelligent.

231
00:12:21,433 --> 00:12:24,167
She's already beautiful and
she's even good at her job.

232
00:12:24,300 --> 00:12:26,300
Hey, hey, hey, Bautista.
Are you becoming a lesbian?

233
00:12:26,433 --> 00:12:29,067
Hey, you're really all nonsense,
aren't you?

234
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:30,633
I'm just impressed with her

235
00:12:30,767 --> 00:12:33,967
because she always helps us
with our cases.

236
00:12:34,100 --> 00:12:35,667
Yes, if you think about it,

237
00:12:35,800 --> 00:12:36,967
she's also the one
who found evidence

238
00:12:37,100 --> 00:12:38,667
and pinpointed Victor Santiago.

239
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:39,767
Do you remember that?

240
00:12:39,900 --> 00:12:43,433
So let's not waste
this lead she gave us.

241
00:12:43,567 --> 00:12:44,900
How could it not be wasted

242
00:12:45,033 --> 00:12:48,767
when we've been looking for any
leads here for a while now.

243
00:12:48,933 --> 00:12:50,867
The sniper did a good job.

244
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:53,333
If we really can't
get a lead here,

245
00:12:53,467 --> 00:12:56,433
maybe we can get
one somewhere else.

246
00:12:56,567 --> 00:12:58,733
Where? What?

247
00:12:58,867 --> 00:13:00,467
Did you see those buildings
over there?

248
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:02,633
Maybe there are
CCTVs over there.

249
00:13:02,767 --> 00:13:04,600
It's possible that the sniper

250
00:13:04,733 --> 00:13:06,200
who was stationed here
was caught in the CCTV.

251
00:13:09,567 --> 00:13:11,600
Bro, what important matter
are we talking about?

252
00:13:11,733 --> 00:13:14,800
I know you're the one
who always helps me,

253
00:13:14,933 --> 00:13:17,567
but I'm sorry.

254
00:13:17,700 --> 00:13:20,300
I'm going to need
your help again.

255
00:13:20,433 --> 00:13:21,900
Wait, what's this about?

256
00:13:22,067 --> 00:13:23,333
Bro...

257
00:13:23,467 --> 00:13:26,300
you already know that I suspect
the Mayor and Ma'am Sophia

258
00:13:26,433 --> 00:13:28,000
that gave orders
